    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                
                <p>I heard, my dear Pupil, at <placeName ref="pl1347">oxford</placeName> of a <persName ref="pe0806">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Astle</persName> 
                    once of the <placeName ref="pl1345">Tower</placeName>, now I think of <placeName ref="pl1346">Lambeth</placeName> who has a fine 
                    collection of drawings of welch monuments: It must be y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> business to find him out, &amp; get a complete list 
                    of all he has.</p>
                
                <p>Be so good as to get from y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> neighbor Buck<note type="editorial">This may refer to 
                    either <persName ref="pe0373">Samuel Buck</persName> or to his brother <persName ref="pe0374">Nathaniel</persName>.</note> a printed list of his prints &amp; send 
                    it in a frank. N. B. get a stock of franks to me.</p>
              
                <p>I leave this place <sic>too day</sic> &amp; shall reach <placeName ref="pl0001">downing</placeName> on 
                    Saturday. am D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir</p>
                <closer><salute>very affect<hi rend="superscript">ly</hi> yrs
                </salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed></closer>
                <dateline><placeName ref="pl1017">Lichfield</placeName> May 21<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> 1771.</dateline>
                
                
         
                
            </div>
            
            <div>      
                <p><address><addrLine>To<lb/><persName ref="pe0803">John Lloyd esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></persName><lb/> 
                    <placeName ref="pl1344">Garden Court</placeName>.
                    </addrLine></address></p>
            </div>
